  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA150-kiḷavi">itu talainiṉṟoḻukappaṭāniṉṟa parattait talaivaṉai neruṅkip pāṇaṟ kuraittatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what the other woman, who kept ???, said to the bard, addressing HIM.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA150">
<l>            nakainaṉ kuṭaiyaṉ pāṇanum perumakaṉ</l>
<l>            miḷaivali citaiyak kaḷiṟupala parappi</l>
<l>            yaraṇpala kaṭanta muraṇko ṭāṉai</l>
<l>            vaḻuti vāḻiya palaveṉat toḻutīṇṭu</l>
<l>            maṉṉeyi luṭaiyōr pōla vaḵtiyā </l>
<l>            meṉṉatum pariyalō vilameṉat taṇṇaṭaik</l>
<l>            kalimā kaṭaii vanteñ cērit</l>
<l>            tāruṅ kaṇṇiyuṅ kāṭṭi yorumaiya</l>
<l>            neñcaṅ koṇṭamai viṭumō vañcak</l>
<l>            kaṇṇuṭaic ciṟukōl paṟṟik </l>
<l>            katamperi tuṭaiyaḷyā yaḻuṅkalō vilaḷē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>He [is] smiling well, bard, your great man.</l>
<l>Does he [now] desert [us], after having taken [our] heart</l>
<l rend="indent">that was one [with him] since he showed a garland and a chaplet</l>
<l rend="indent">in our quarter, having come, inciting the proud horses,</l>
<l rend="indent3">into the village, saying</l>
<l rend="indent2">“as for us having any distress about that, we have none”,</l>
<l rend="indent">as those who possess a permanent fortress here worship</l>
<l rend="indent3">[with the words]</l>
<l rend="indent2">“may Vaḻuti live many [days], with [his] enemy-taking army</l>
<l rend="indent2">that has surmounted many a stronghold, having spread a number</l>
<l rend="indent2">of(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kaḷiṟu pala</term>? - <term xml:lang="ta">araṇ pala</term>: usually <term xml:lang="ta">pal</term> is preceding its word of reference. What precisely is expressed by this double change of word order?</note> elephant bulls to waste [their] strength on the enclosure”?</l>
<l rend="indent3">Seizing the small jointed rod of bamboo(?)</l>
<l>she has great anger: mother, as for being [just] noisy – not she.</l>
        </lg>
